pacman/yay:

Use pacman for the official repository, use yay for AUR (Arch User Repository)

System update:
pacman -Syu
yay -Syua (can be slow, needs to build packages)

Search:
pacman -Ss
yay -Ss

Search offline:
pacman -Qs
yay -Qs

Install:
pacman -S
yay -S

Remove:
pacman -R
yay -R

List:
pacman -Ql
yay -Ql

List installed packages:
pacman -Qm
yay -Qm

List orphans:
pacman -Qtdq

Remove orphans:
pacman -Rs $(pacman -Qtdq)

Clean:
pacman -Sc

Install old package:
pacman -U /path/to/package
but try `downgrade package` first

To set pacman to a specific date, modify and uncomment lines at bottom in
/etc/pacman.conf
comment the other databases and run
pacman -Syyuu

Find out to which package ${file} belongs to
pacman -Qo ${file}

See update history
/var/log/pacman.log

Download fresh package database from server
pacman -Fy

Find what package provides file (like yum whatprovides)
pacman -Fs ${filename}
pacman -Fo ${pathname}

Find what package provides file using regexes (like yum whatprovides)
pacman -Fs ${regexfilename}
pacman -Fo ${regexpathname}

See dependency tree of a package
pactree ${package}
